OL,3,CTributes paid to 'Sir Fab' - the
OL,4,CLieutenant Governor who was full of fun
OL,6,FRichard Graham served as his secretary
OL,7,Fand aide-de-camp throughout this time
OL,8,F- with the pair both working together
OL,9,Fand living side-by-side at Government
OL,10,FHouse.
OL,12,F"He was really rather special",
OL,13,FRichard remembers.
OL,15,F"There was a great sense of fun about
OL,16,Fhim - he liked people, and they liked
OL,17,Fhim.
OL,19,F"He got around the Bailiwicks, and
OL,20,Fenjoyed going to the other islands and
OL,21,Fmeeting people there."
