OL,3,CTributes paid to 'Sir Fab' - the
OL,4,CLieutenant Governor who was full of fun
OL,6,FRichard adds Sir Fabian always wanted
OL,7,Fto be involved in community events and
OL,8,Fsay yes to requests - and he often had
OL,9,Fto spend time reminding the Governor
OL,10,Fwhy he couldn't do all that was asked
OL,11,Fof him.
OL,13,FHowever, he remembers he would always
OL,14,Fgo the extra mile to do his best for
OL,15,Fthe Bailiwick.
