OL,3,CTributes paid to 'Sir Fab' - the
OL,4,CLieutenant Governor who was full of fun
OL,6,F"Every now and then there would be
OL,7,Ftensions - often political tensions
OL,8,Fbetween the UK and the islands - and
OL,9,Falthough this would usually be up to
OL,10,Fthe Chief Minister or Bailiff to deal
OL,11,Fwith, he would sometimes pick up the
OL,12,Fphone and call people he knew in the
OL,13,FUK and try his best to smooth things
OL,14,Fover, or encourage them to sort it
OL,15,Fout", he explains.
OL,17,FSir Fabian was a keen photographer,
OL,18,Fand spent a great deal of his spare
OL,19,Ftime out and about in the island using
OL,20,Fhis camera to capture the island's
OL,21,Fbeauty.
