OL,3,CTributes paid to 'Sir Fab' - the
OL,4,CLieutenant Governor who was full of fun
OL,6,FRichard adds that he was a kind and
OL,7,Fpatient man - the only time he saw him
OL,8,Firritated was when someone spelt his
OL,9,Fname incorrectly, with an 'o' instead
OL,10,Fof a second 'a'.
OL,12,F"I think that was only something that
OL,13,Fhad happened throughout his life, and
OL,14,Fit was usually when he thought, they
OL,15,Fshould know better", he explains.
OL,17,FRichard also remembers Sir Fabian
OL,18,Fbeing very competitive.
