OL,3,CTributes paid to 'Sir Fab' - the
OL,4,CLieutenant Governor who was full of fun
OL,6,FIn his second year, he wanted to take
OL,7,Fon the annual round island walk -
OL,8,FRichard persuaded him to take on the
OL,9,Fhalf distance first, but he did the
OL,10,Ffull distance the following year.
OL,12,F"Although he was limping a the end, he
OL,13,Fdid it without much problem.
OL,15,F"Three months later he was in Sir
OL,16,FThomas' in London having a quadruple
OL,17,Fheart operation. That was in the
OL,18,FAutumn, and in the following June he
OL,19,Fwas back doing the half island walk -
OL,20,Fhe was a very determined person."
